- Check if stack is full before pushing (`if (top == capacity - 1)`) <marks>1</marks>
- Add item to top of stack using pre-increment (`stack[++top] = value;`) <marks>1</marks>
- Method signature for `pop` (`public int pop()`) <marks>1</marks>
- Check if stack is empty before popping (`if (top == -1)`) <marks>1</marks>
- Remove and return item from top using post-decrement (`return stack[top--];`) <marks>1</marks>

**Note:** Full implementation for reference:
```java
public class Stack {
    private int[] stack;
    private int top = -1; 
    private int capacity;

    public Stack(int capacity) {
        this.capacity = capacity;
        stack = new int[capacity];
    }

    public void push(int value) {
        if (top == capacity - 1) {
            return;
        }
        stack[++top] = value;
    }

    public int pop() {
        if (top == -1) {
            return -1;
        }
        return stack[top--];
    }
}
```

